<head>ABYSS</head>
    <list type="translations">
        <item xml:lang="zh">深淵</item>
    </list>
<div type="definition">

    <p resp="#CH" modified="2020-10-16T16:29:17.815+09:00">ROCK LANDSCAPE that is INTENSELY AND STEEP AND CONTAINS WATER AT THE BOTTOM. </p>
        <div type="definition" resp="#CH" modified="2022-07-20T18:58:52.521+09:00">
            <p>ROCK LANDSCAPE that is INTENSELY DEEP AND STEEP AND CONTAINS WATER AT the BOTTOM.</p>
        </div>
    </div>
<div type="notes">
<div type="old-chinese-criteria">
<p>[POETIC/PROSAIC]</p>
<p>1. The general poetic word for a deep and threatening watery abyss is yuān 淵.</p>
<p>[POETIC]</p>
<p>2. Tán 潭 is also refers to a deep and threatening watery abyss.</p>
<p>3. Huò 壑 can refer to a steep deep valley or abyss. The distinction with VALLEY is often unclear.</p>
<p>[PROSAIC]</p>
        </div>
<div type="modern-chinese-criteria">
