<title>Lateinische Synonyme und Etymologien</title>
                <note>
<p>ABYSS</p>
<p>vorago is a poetical and foreign word for a deep abyss.</p>
<p>barathrum refers to an abyss in water, which may be either in a pool, pond, or sea.</p>
<p>vortex refers to deep water in motion.</p>
<p>gurges refers to a vortex which moves in a perpendicular direction so that it drags down whatever comes into its eddy.</p>
                </note>
